# Conciencia Inquieta — MVP Build Plan

A self-managed digital magazine. This document is the build roadmap to the MVP.
For day-to-day working rules and conventions, see `CLAUDE.md`.

---

## The objective

**One job: turn visitors into subscribers.** Own the audience (an email list plus one broadcast channel), and measure everything. Prove there is genuine interest before building anything heavier.

Marie's following is currently *rented* from the social platforms. Content is the reason to visit; the **email signup is the asset**. Community, membership and shop come later — only when there is evidence the audience shows up.

---

## Approach & key decisions

- **Reuse, don't rebuild.** Fork the Astro-Psyche Lab backend (Supabase + custom admin) into a **new, separate CI Supabase project**. Copy the pattern, not the instance. (Code is Lewis's to reuse.)
- **Inherited features stay hidden for the MVP.** The fork includes **service price management** and **content-generation tools**. Both are **flagged OFF** via a code-managed boolean config (Lewis-only). They will be revealed to Marie one-by-one for testing/verification *after* the MVP ships.
- **Article upload is currently basic** and will be extended into a proper magazine content model (categories, tags, author, subtitle, featured image, reading time, related).
- **Architecture:** the public site is **static Astro built from content in Supabase**. The only database-backed surface in the MVP is the **admin/CMS** (Marie logs in to post). **No end-user accounts or payments in the MVP.**
- **Email:** MailerLite — reuse the integration code, but on **CI's own account/audience**, never co-mingled with another client's list. (The whole thesis is Marie *owning* her audience.)
- **Hosting:** Vercel, on the generic `*.vercel.app` subdomain first. Custom domain transfer is **out of MVP**.
- **Standing rules:** never migrate production (staging-first), one Supabase project per product, reference exact files in session prompts, keep a rolling `lessons.md`, CLI-first.

---

## MVP scope — IN

- Static Astro public site: Home, Article template, Category pages, About, **"Únete"** landing, Contact, legal pages
- Magazine content model + admin so Marie self-publishes
- Inherited backend, with non-MVP features flagged off
- **Email list signup (primary CTA)** with double opt-in
- **One broadcast channel (secondary CTA)** — WhatsApp Channel or Telegram
- Lead-magnet delivery on signup (plumbing now, asset later)
- Cookieless analytics + Meta Pixel + consent banner (CMP)
- UTM convention for social links
- SEO, performance, accessibility, responsive baseline
- Legal: privacy, cookies, terms

## Explicitly OUT of MVP (later / v2+)

- End-user accounts & login, saved articles
- Membership / subscription billing, manage-subscription
- Shop / e-commerce (catalog, cart, checkout, payments, confirmation emails)
- Google Ads
- On-site community / comments
- Internal search *(v2)*
- Services section *(v2 — inquiry-based, no checkout)*
- **GoDaddy → custom-domain transfer** *(separate later task; preserve MX/email, watch parked A-records + domain forwarding, use delegate access)*
- Revealing the flagged service-pricing / content-generation features *(post-MVP, one by one)*

